HEADWORD: Unbefool
<hw>Un`be*fool"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>befool</ets>.]</ety> <def>To deliver from the
state of a fool; to awaken the mind of; to undeceive.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

